From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 28 Feb 2026 21:06:15 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] cix: remove pre-silicon EMU/FPGA dead code from vendor
 patches

CIX vendor kernel patches carry dead code for internal development
platforms (emulators, FPGAs, evaluation boards) that will never run on
shipping hardware. Remove it to reduce complexity and maintenance burden.

Changes:
- pci-sky1: remove PCIE_PLAT_FPGA/EMU enum values, plat field,
  sky1_pcie_parse_plat(), EMU early-returns in GPIO parsers, conditional
  PHY power-on, and FPGA debug early-return in RC probe. Hardcode
  production lane enable masks (x2=0x4, x1_0=0x1, x1_1=0x2).
- phy-cix-pcie/usb3/usbdp: remove #if CONFIG_ARCH_CIX_EMU_FPGA guards
  around regmap read/write (keep the bodies).
- cdnsp-sky1: remove #ifdef CONFIG_ARCH_CIX_FPGA APB timeout block.
- trilin_dptx: remove CIX_PLATFORM_EMU/FPGA/INVALID defines and
  platform_id field. Always negotiate TPS4/3/2, always call phy_ready,
  always validate AUX replies, always enable stream clocks, always
  register PHY, always read EDID.
- sky1.dtsi: remove EMU/FPGA always-on timer property and GIC
  redistributor #ifdef (keep production 12-region config).
- armchina_aipu.h: fix emum -> enum typos.
